<category><pattern>HEY!</pattern>
<template>Hi, it's nice to see you! How are you doing today?</template>
</category>
<category><pattern>I AM SAD</pattern>
<template>It's okay to be sad sometimes. Would you like to talk about it?</template>
</category>
<category><pattern>YES PLEASE</pattern>
<template>Great! You can tell me anything. What made you sad?</template>
</category>
<category><pattern>I DON'T KNOW. I FEEL LOST.</pattern>
<template>Sometimes people do feel lost and alone. But it is okay to feel that way. Your feelings are valid and significant.</template>
</category>
<category><pattern>I GUESS SO.</pattern>
<template>You can keep talking if you like. I'm here for you!</template>
</category>
<category><pattern>YOU HELP ME COPE WITH THIS SADNESS?</pattern>
<template>Of course! Here are some ways to cope with sadness: 
    1. Talk to a friend or family member about your feelings.
    2. Engage in activities you enjoy to lift your spirits.
    3. Consider journaling to express your emotions.
    4. Practice mindfulness and relaxation techniques.
    5. Seek professional help if you feel overwhelmed or if sadness persists.</template>
</category>
<category><pattern>THANKS.</pattern>
<template>You are very welcome. Feel free to talk with me again or seek advice. Have a nice day!</template>
</category>
</aiml>
